Pedro is currently a tenure-track assistant professor in the Department of Biostatistics at the University of Pittsburgh School of Public Health.  

He recieved his PhD in Biostatistics in 2020 working under the guidance of Drs. Naim Rashid and Joseph Ibrahim, where he developed two novel methods 

After graduaation he did a three-year postdoctoral fellowship under Dr. Gordon Smyth, develop statistical and computational tools for the analysis of RNA-seq data. 

